    widget. The calling object then uses that value, ANDed with the mask <I>y</I>, as its input. This 
    method is only valid if the intrinsic value&nbsp;is a byte or word. The 
    mask <I>y</I> can be either a byte or word. This allows 
    a Control object to provide the input to a View Widget. This method is called 
    from a View Widget href.</li>
    <li><B>nextEntry()</B> - Highlighted box of a list box widget moves to next 
    entry in the list. Effectively moves the highlighted box down one entry. 
    Does NOT automatically perform a &quot;hit&quot; method.</li>
  <li><B>previousEntry()</B> - Highlighted box of a list box widget moves to 
    previous&nbsp;entry in the list. Effectively moves the highlighted box up&nbsp;one 
    entry. Does NOT automatically perform a &quot;hit&quot; method.</li>
  <li><B>reappear()</B> - Makes the List visible and touchable on the LCD. Counteracts 
    the disappear() method.</li>
